tourBios.carHigh: 2011: Has been granted a Minor Medical extension but has not teed it up since playing in two events in 2008. 2009: Did not play on the Web.com Tour. 2008: Made two starts on the Web.com Tour, missing the cut in both. Missed the cut at the AT&T Classic in his lone PGA TOUR start. Member of the Web.com Tour in 2003-04. Has made just two starts since the 2004 season, with only made cutâa T43 at the 2005 Preferred Health Systems Wichita Open. 2004: Made the cut in 11 of 24 starts, with a career-best T10 at the Miccosukee Championship. 2003: Made the cut in two of 14 starts during his rookie season, with a 67th-place finish at the Albertsons Boise Open his best outing. Has never played in a PGA TOUR event. Long-time member of the Hooters Tour where he enjoyed one of his best seasons in 2002, making the cut in 15 of 18 starts, with six top-10s. Finished No. 14 on the money list, with $37,839. Best outing was a runner-up finish at the Wilmington, NC, event, losing to former Web.com Tour player Jeremy Wilkinson by one stroke. Most recently, has posted eight top-25 finishes on that Tour from 2005-07. Has also played on the Moonlight Tour and the Tommy Armour Tour.
tourBios.personal: Father, who he lists as his hero, got him started in the game as a youngster...Cites playing with the "fellas" on the Web.com Tour as his biggest thrill in golf.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T10th in 2004 at the Miccosukee Championship.
